<TITLE> Obama invites Hasina </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 9 (bdnews24.com)--US president Barack Obama has invited prime minister Sheikh Hasina to attend a programme in New York slated for Sept 23. US ambassador James F Moriarty handed the invitation letter to prime minister Sheikh Hasina on Wednesday, the prime minister's press secretary Abul Kalam Azad told reporters after a meeting. Obama invited the heads of the government of the 10 UN peace-keeping countries who contributed best to the mission. Bangladesh has the second highest contribution in the mission. Moriarty thanked the prime minister for the sympathy Bangladesh showed after the death of senior US senator Edward M Kennedy. Hasina said Bangladesh would remember forever Kennedy's role during the war of independence, the press secretary said. bd
